description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Health England will provide strategic leadership and vision for protecting and improving the nation’s health. Its ambition is to lead nationally and enable locally a transformation in the health expectations of all people in England regardless of where they live and the circumstance of their birth. It will achieve this through the application of research, knowledge and skills. Public Health England is an executive agency of the Department of Health, which started on 1 April 2013. We are a distinct delivery organisation with operational autonomy to advise and support Government, local authorities and the NHS in a professionally independent manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Disease Registration division will provide the teams and expertise, in partnership with other groups across PHE and beyond, to collect, collate and quality-assure large population-level datasets for specific diseases and conditions. The division already has responsibility for the National Cancer Registration Service. The aim of the disease registration division is to become an international leader in population-based disease registration, surveillance and monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Cancer Registration Officer, you will be part of a team that collects patient level data that is used to influence improvement in patient outcomes, show which treatments give the best results, and to enable NHS Commissioning to target resources where they most benefit patients. The data that you collect also provides the basis for research, prevention strategies, effectiveness of screening programmes, and the national statistics on cancer incidence, survival and mortality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to make a difference to the one in two of us who will either receive a diagnosis of cancer, or know someone who has. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Civil Service is an equal opportunity employer which promotes flexible working and offers an attractive work environment with excellent benefits and pension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a desire to ‘make a difference’, have excellent attention to detail, and an inquisitive and inquiring mind – this is the job for you. Training will be provided that leads to a Public Health Diploma in Cancer Registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the shortlisting process you will be asked to complete an online test. Details of this will be sent electronically via your email address, once the advert has closed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are strongly advised to use the criteria in the person specification (available online) as sub-headings in their application to make it clear how they meet each of the selection criteria. Please also see job description for competencies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Health England promotes diversity in the workplace and is an equal opportunities employer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Option 3 – External&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open to all external applicants (anyone) from outside the Civil Service (including by definition internal applicants).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We welcome and encourage applications from everyone, including groups currently underrepresented in our workforce and pride ourselves as being an employer of choice.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To find out more about how we champion diversity and inclusion in the workplace, visit: PHE Website&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On 18 August 2020, the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care announced plans to establish the National Institute of Health Protection and consult on the best future options for strengthening health improvement and other public health functions in the wider system. Public Health England and its employees will be in scope for transition to new organisations in Spring 2021. Any new or current employees working for Public Health England during this time, will receive appropriate consultation prior to any formal transfer taking place.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Carlos Rocha Job title Registration Manager Email address Carlos.Rocha@phe.co.uk Telephone number 02084 953732&lt;/p&gt;
